Extensions/UITableView.html#/s:So11UITab.name: dequeue(_:)
Extensions/UITableView.html#/s:So11UITab.abstract: Dequeue cell of given class from tableView.

Extensions/UICollectionView.html#/s:So16.name: dequeue(_:indexPath:)
Extensions/UICollectionView.html#/s:So16.abstract: Dequeue cell of given class from tableView.

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: duration
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: The duration of the video in seconds.

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: zoom
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: The zoom of the timeline view. The higher zoom value, the more accurate rewind is. Default is 1.0.

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: intervalWidth
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: The width of a line representing a specific time interval on a timeline. If zoom is not equal 1, then actual interval width equals to intervalWidth * zoom. Value will be used during rewind for calculations — for example, if zoom is 1, intervalWidth is 30 and intervalDuration is 15, then when user moves 10pixels left or right we will rewind by +5 or -5 seconds;

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: intervalDuration
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: The duration of an interval in seconds. If video is 55 seconds and interval is 15 seconds — then we will have 3 full intervals and one not full interval. Value will be used during rewind for calculations.

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: currentTimeDidChange
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: Block which will be triggered everytime currentTime value changes.

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: timeIntervalFromDistance(_:)
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: Calculates time interval in seconds from passed width.

Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.name: rewindByDistance(_:)
Classes/TimelineView.html#/s:5Natty12Tim.abstract: Rewinds by distance. Calculates interval width and adds it to the current time.
